<CHANGES>
###1.1.0
- Fix: remove -r flag from newest_snapshot() and find_base_snapshot_for_incremental() — parent datasets now upload correctly
- Fix: config source ordering — all defaults use ${var:-default} so user config values are no longer silently overridden
- Fix: autosnapshots default changed from "no" to "yes" — backups now work on fresh installs without manual config editing
- Fix: --dry-run no longer writes to state file, preventing broken incremental chains
- Fix: install.sh adds /boot/config/go entries for reboot persistence — scripts survive reboots without manual intervention
- Fix: rclone config path corrected to /boot/config/rclone/rclone.conf (persistent across reboots)
- Fix: sanoid/sanoid.conf reduced to dataset-only section — no longer duplicates template sections in system sanoid.conf
- Fix: uninstall.sh removes go file entries and references correct rclone path
- Fix: config variable name source_dataset_auto_select_exclude corrected to source_dataset_auto_select_exclude_prefix
- Docs: added Critical Notes section covering boot persistence, rclone path, autosnapshots, Google Advanced Protection Program, and service account auth setup
###1.0.8
- Fix: Unversioned zfs-gdrsync.plg added at repo root — Unraid update detection now works
- Fix: Self-healing on reboot — rclone config symlink and sanoid global config are recreated if missing
###1.0.7
- Fix: incremental sends now marked with _I_ suffix in filename — enables prune logic to distinguish full vs incremental archives
- Fix: corrected typo in log message (undefined variable days_since_full_ge)
- Change: rewrite prune_gdrive_dataset() to implement: keep most recent full snapshot always (no age limit), prune full snapshots older than gdrive_retention_days, prune old incrementals
- Docs: added detailed prune policy explanation to plugin/config comments
###1.0.6
- Fix: install script deploys to /root/zfs-gdrsync/ (ext4) as canonical location — FAT32 /boot does not support execute bits
- Fix: User Scripts entry now points to /root/zfs-gdrsync/zfs-gdrsync.sh
- Docs: updated all manual command examples to use /root/zfs-gdrsync/ path
- Uninstall: now removes /root/zfs-gdrsync/zfs-gdrsync.sh
###1.0.5
- Fix: removed Mode attribute from FILE elements — chmod fails on FAT boot filesystem (no Unix permissions)
</CHANGES>
